dataIdInfo.idAbs: Generalised Land Use Database Boundaries 2001 (GLUD) are experimental maps on land use for all of England. GLUD Boundaries maps are derived from, and a summary of, detailed land parcel level GLUD maps. The methodology to produce the land parcel level GLUD allocated all identifiable features (TOIDs) on Ordnance Survey's MasterMap(r) into one of nine simplified categories: Domestic Buildings, Gardens, Non-Domestic Buildings, Road, Rail, Path, Greenspace, Water, and Other. A small residual of land parcels may remain Unclassified. The summary GLUD Boundaries maps have been produced from the detailed TOID level GLUD maps by 'dissolving' the TOID outlines. GLUD Boundaries 2001 maps support the development of Sustainable Communities and Neighbourhood Renewal and are a foundational dataset on the availability of Greenspace for the 'Cleaner, Safer, Greener' agenda and the 'Greenspace Database'. GLUD maps are a product of a programme of work that has also delivered GLUD statistics for the Office for National Statistics' Neighbourhood Statistics programme.
